                Find a zero near the midpoint of {@code min} and {@code max}.                
                <@param>
                    m f Function to solve.                    
                </@param>
                <@param>
                    m min Lower bound for the interval.                    
                </@param>
                <@param>
                    m max Upper bound for the interval.                    
                </@param>
                <@param>
                    m maxEval Maximum number of evaluations.                    
                </@param>
                <@return>
                    n the value where the function is zero.                    
                </@return>
                <@throws>
                    s org.apache.commons.math3.exception.TooManyEvaluationsExceptionif the maximum evaluation count is exceeded.                    
                </@throws>
                <@throws>
                    s org.apache.commons.math3.exception.NumberIsTooLargeExceptionif {@code min >= max}.                    
                </@throws>
